Our app uses a dedicated background service to accurately detect call events—such as missed, incoming, and outgoing calls—and capture key details like phone number, date, and time. This ensures users always have a complete and reliable record of their call activity. The service automatically starts when a call begins and stops as soon as the call ends, minimizing resource usage and preserving privacy. Once a call is finished, it securely syncs the call history with the app in real time, so no data is lost and every feature dependent on call activity works seamlessly without delays.

This service enhances the user experience by providing a seamless and persistent interface for adding notes after a call ends. It achieves this by: Maintaining UI state: The service preserves the note-taking interface even when the app is in the background, ensuring that users don\'t lose any data or context. Quick launch via notification: A notification provides a convenient shortcut for users to access the note-taking interface instantly, allowing for immediate capture of important information. Data preservation: By keeping the UI active and accessible, the service safeguards user data and prevents accidental loss due to app closure or background processes. This approach prioritizes user convenience and data integrity, ensuring a smooth and efficient note-taking experience after calls.
